  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Resistance training as well as creatine supplementation may be beneficial for cognitive
      function, such as memory and attention. Therefore, the investigators speculate that
      resistance training combined with creatine supplementation would promote additive benefits on
      cognitive function in elderly women.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
